# Documentation Authoring

When editing files under `docs/`:

- Preserve authoritative tone; these docs are executed by AI agents on M4 hardware.
- Use complete markdown: headings, tables, code blocks — never one-line stubs.
- Cross-link related docs using backtick filenames (e.g. `OSLab_Program_Board.md`).
- Keep `docs/Project_Index_Alalā.md` status column accurate when adding or completing docs.
- After doc changes that affect project status, update @docs/OSLab_Program_Board.md.
- Do not create meta/staging files (`filename.md`, `OtherKeyFiles.md`).
- HCA and IPJ references must align with @docs/Alalā_Core_Invariant_Specification_HCA.md and @docs/IPJ_Measurement_Protocol_Alalā.md.

Verification: `./verify.sh` checks all 22 indexed docs exist and are >200 bytes.
